                                    &#160;</div></ulink></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para>In this way, we divide a whole bibliographical entry into three parts: </para><ul><li>The core <span class="publication">Publication</span> data. In the case of a monograph, this may be all the information one can supply, if the monograph does not occur as part of a
                series. </li><li>The publication <span class="container">Container</span>. In the case of a monograph, the publication container is typically a monograph series.</li><li>The <span class="location">Location</span> of the publication inside the container. In the case of a monograph, this is the identification of where inside the series the
                publication occurs, that is, its volume number.</li></ul><para>We shall see that this way of disposing a bibliographical entry applies equally to publications inside periodicals and edited volumes.</para></chapter></book>